description:
This video is a Polymer Clay tutorial on how to bake and cure polymer clay correctly. This is one of the topics that we get the most queries on as underbaked or overbaked polymer clay is a common issue. We will answer your common questions about:
- Should my polymer clay be flexible?
- Baking temperature
- Baking time
- Oven Thermometer
- Oven preheating
- How to test your polymer clay pieces
- What type of oven to bake in
- Do you need to tent your pieces?

To find a range of polymer clay and resin supplies, head to our website www.myclayco.com.au

If you have any questions about our video, we're happy to help - just comment below :) 

Wed love for you to like, share and subscribe for more fun and instructional videos!

You can also find us on 
Instagram: instagram.com/myclayco
Facebook: https://www.Facebook.com/myclayco.com.au
TikTok: TikTok.com/@myclayco
Pinterest: https://www.pinterest.com.au/myclayco

If you have any tutorial or create with me suggestions wed love to hear from you! Contact us via our socials or email us at hello@myclayco.com.au

You can also subscribe to our newsletter via our website www.myclayco.com.au to get exclusive discounts, maker news, and product updates. 

Thanks for watching and happy making!
The MyClayCo Team x
